# Release TypeScript build validation

PR quality typecheck (`scripts/ci/tsconfig.typecheck.json`) maps `@node-webrtc-rust/bindings` to **`packages/bindings/index.d.ts`** (workspace contract).

Release publish runs **`scripts/ci/build-ts-workspace.sh`**, which compiles SDK sources with the same module graph npm uses after `npm ci`. A stale **registry** copy of `@node-webrtc-rust/bindings` under `packages/sdk/node_modules/` can shadow the workspace package and make release fail with errors like:

- `Property 'addTransceiver' does not exist on type 'JsPeerConnection'`
- `Module '"@node-webrtc-rust/bindings"' has no exported member 'JsVoiceAgent'`

`run-pr-quality.sh` alone (typecheck only) will **not** catch this.

## Required before commit (release / SDK / bindings / CI changes)

From `node-webrtc-rust/`:

```bash
bash scripts/ci/run-pr-quality.sh
bash scripts/ci/verify-release-publish-ts.sh
```

When Docker is available (matches remote ci-build container):

```bash
npm run ci:verify:release-ts:docker
```

That script runs **`build-ts-workspace.sh`** after typecheck. Do not skip it when touching release publish, SDK tsconfig, or workspace dependency pins.

## SDK tsconfig

`packages/sdk/tsconfig.json` maps `@node-webrtc-rust/bindings` to `packages/bindings/index.d.ts` so release publish does not typecheck against a stale registry copy under `packages/sdk/node_modules/`.

- SDK workspace deps use semver pins in package.json; `set-release-deps.sh` rewrites them at publish time.
- `packages/sdk/tsconfig.json` keeps a `paths` entry for `@node-webrtc-rust/bindings` → `packages/bindings/index.d.ts` so tsc always uses the committed NAPI contract (not a stale registry copy under `packages/sdk/node_modules/`).
